    {
      "source": "evaluator",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:\n\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n}\n\nany idea why it's overlapping on small screens?"
    },
    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it seems like the product image is taking up more space than the title text, causing the overlap on mobile devices. Try adjusting the `flex-grow` property of the `.product-image` class. This will allow the image to grow and take up only the space it needs, leaving room for the title text. Here's an updated snippet:\n\n```css\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n  flex-grow: 1;\n}\n\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n}\n```\n\nThis should fix the overlapping issue on mobile devices. Let me know if you need any more help!",
